00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:07.800
How to Make Beef Fajitas

00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:10.500
Serves: 12 

00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:13.300
Ingredients for the marinade

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:15.000
Juice of 1 orange

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.400
Juice of 2 limes

00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:20.100
3 tbsp olive oil

00:00:20.100 --> 00:00:22.200
2 garlic cloves, minced

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:27.200
1 hot green chili pepper, seeded and finely minced

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:31.300
2 tbsp fresh coriander, finely chopped

00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:34.500
½ tsp cumin

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:37.500
½ tsp sweet paprika

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:40.600
½ tsp black pepper

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:42.800
1 tsp salt

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:44.500
Ingredients for the fajitas

00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:47.800
1 kg beef steak

00:00:47.800 --> 00:00:54.500
3 peppers (red, green and yellow), seeded and thinly sliced

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:59.000
1 red onion, cut in half and finely chopped

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.100
12 tortillas bread, warm

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:05.000
Directions for the marinade

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:16.000
In a bowl whisk together the orange and lemon juice, olive oil, minced garlic, green chili pepper, coriander

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:24.100
cumin, sweet paprika, black pepper and salt.

00:01:24.100 --> 00:01:31.300
Place the beef steaks in a shallow dish and pour the marinade over.

00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:35.000
Cover and chill overnight in the fridge. 

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:36.500
Directions for the fajitas

00:01:36.500 --> 00:01:46.500
Heat a large pan over high heat, grill the steaks for 3-5 minutes on each side, depending how you like it.

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:53.500
Let the meat rest a minute then cut into slices.

00:01:53.500 --> 00:02:04.000
Add the peppers and onions to the same pan and cook until tender and slightly browned.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.300
Return the meat to the same pan and cook for 1 minute.

00:02:08.300 --> 00:02:15.000
Serve the Fajitas with tortilla bread and some Pico de Gallo salsa and some sour cream. 

